		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Pto Cabello</placeName> <date>24 March 1854</date>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqr</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have the pleasure to acknowledge the receipt<lb/> of your favor of <date>23d</date> last covering b&#47;Ly for 1 box containing<lb/> 2 cops bibles&#44; 1 do <sic>payer</sic> books 1 do Bible and two do <persName>Dias</persName><lb/> letters per Paez&#44; <persName>Capt<hi rend="sup">n</hi> Wilkins</persName> amtg to &#36;66.37 &#189; for which<lb/> together with the contribution to the Occident for the com<lb/>ing year&#44; I beg leave to enclose a draft on <persName>Messrs Dallett<lb/> Brothers</persName> at your port say &#36;69.384. The bibles and<lb/> prayerbooks were all to my liking&#44; only in the prospec<lb/>tus sent to you please to observe that only one copy was<lb/> ordered with any name&#59; fortunately it happened that<lb/> the other was for a very particular and intimate friend<lb/> of mine&#44; who would have no objection to take it even<lb/> with my name&#44; as he did without hesitancy. One copy<lb/> of <persName>Dias&#39;</persName> letters I took for myself&#44; and the other toge<lb/>ther with the unordered copy of the bible was taken<lb/> by <persName>Mr Jacob Julien</persName> of this place&#59; and I will try to dis<lb/>pose of some of your books among my friends here &#38;<lb/> about&#44; and succeeding which I sincerely hope I may&#44;<lb/> I will immediately advise you of the same.</p>
			<p><hi rend="underline">On the</hi></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
          <p rend="indent(1)">On the <date>24 of January</date> last I wrote you per <persName>Dallett</persName><lb/> enclosing a list of some school books and other works to<lb/> which I have received no answer&#44; so I suppose the letter<lb/> did not come to hand before your last. Please to favour<lb/> me with your answer at your earliest convenience and<lb/> believe me</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)">Yours Sincerely</p>
          <p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">A Myerston</persName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><hi rend="underline">Bark &#8220;Daer&#8221;</hi></p>
			<p><addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqre</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>371 Walnut Street</placeName></p>
